    b"{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0a\x0a        Choose memory search hints for the selected task "
    b"and current request.\x0a\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before the sele"
    b"cted task runs.\x0a\x0a        Stop once the hints look good enough for the request wi"
    b"thout thinking about it too much.\x0a\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0a        - tags: exac"
    b"t memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0a        - strings.contains: case"
    b"-insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0a          as a substring agai"
    b"nst searchable memory content.\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Each"
    b" value is checked for exact\x0a          equality against searchable memory content"
    b".\x0a\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: "
    b"a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a    "
    b"    Rules:\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidate_memory.\x0a   "
    b"     - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0a  "
    b"        when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_"
    b"of for positive tag hints.\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibilit"
    b"y with older memories needs it.\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclus"
    b"ions.\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable words or phrases that should ap"
    b"pear\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0a        - Use strings.equals only for e"
    b"xact text that should match a relevant\x0a          memory value as a whole.\x0a      "
    b"  - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints over broad keyword stuffing.\x0a       "
    b" - Return empty arrays when no useful search hint is available.\x0a        - Use op"
    b"tional outputs only when they are useful.\x0a\x0a        {{ _.role(\"user\") }}\x0a\x0a       "
    b" Current user request:\x0a        {{ current_user_request }}\x0a\x0a        Conversation "
